# 1. Ignore everything by default
*

# 2. Allow Git to traverse into directories to look for configs
!*/

# 3. CRITICAL: Absolutely block external, dependency, and cache folders
# Git will completely skip scanning anything inside these folders
**/node_modules/
**/raw/docs/
**/.ci/
**/.circleci/
**/.github/
**/.vscode/
**/.devcontainer/
**/android/
**/ios/

# 4. Whitelist only your specific PIOS workspace files by exact name
!**/manifest.yaml
!**/CLAUDE.md
!**/SYSTEM.md
!**/BEHAVIOR.md
!**/SKILLS.md
!**/STATE.md
!**/TASKS.md
!**/REVIEW.md
!**/API.md
!**/README.md
!**/PRIVACY.md
!**/INDEX.md
!**/KNOWLEDGE.md
!**/ONTOLOGY.md
!**/DECISIONS.md
!**/IDEAS.md
!**/ROADMAP.md
!**/ARCHITECTURE.md
!**/CHANGELOG.md
!**/DEPENDENCIES.md

# 6. Ensure this .gitignore itself is tracked
!.gitignore
